    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Celadon stoneware produced in kilns in the town of Longquan (province of Zhejiang), China, from the Song to the mid-Qing dynasties (roughly from the 11th to the 18th century).</Note_Text>
